Story: help message of 'node list'
  As a cluster administrator
  I want to read help message of node list command
  So that I can understand how to get a list of nodes


  Scenario: node help list
    When I run './node help list'

    Then the first line of help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of '-t' and '--trace' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-v' and '--verbose' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-h' and '--help' option


  Scenario: node list --help
    When I run './node list --help'

    Then the first line of help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of '-t' and '--trace' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-v' and '--verbose' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-h' and '--help' option


  Scenario: node list -h
    When I run './node list -h'

    Then the first line of help message should be a usage example
    And the help message should include a description of '-t' and '--trace' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-v' and '--verbose' option
    And the help message should include a description of '-h' and '--help' option
